   Web and Internet Questions
   QUESTION MARK In looking over the Indian Health Service web site, I
   sometimes encounter incorrect or outdated information or receive an
   error message. To whom should I report these errors?
   QUESTION MARK If you have questions about the Internet and World Wide
   Web, our Web Site Help Center F A Q page may have your answers.
   QUESTION MARK For informations on web servers, browser issues, I H S
   Best Practices and Policies for the Internet, and other documentation
   on the design and constructions of web sites, see the Webmaster Help
   page.
   QUESTION MARK If you have comments or questions regarding the
   development, content, or operation of the I H S World Wide Web site or
   servers, please send e-mail to Webmaster@ihs.gov. Your message will be
   routed to an appropriate member of the I H S Web Team.
   QUESTION MARK For comments and questions of a general nature that are
   not covered in these F A Q's, please send an e-mail to
   Feedback@ihs.gov. Your message will be routed to the appropriate I H S
   Office, Area, or Program.

